OL,4,Cconvictions overturned at Supreme Court
OL,6,FHe added: "Mr Hayes was entitled to
OL,7,Fhave his defence to the allegation
OL,8,Fthat he agreed to procure false
OL,9,Fsubmissions as well as his denial that
OL,10,Fhe had acted dishonestly left fairly
OL,11,Fto the jury."
OL,13,FHe was deprived of that opportunity by
OL,14,Fdirections which were legally
OL,15,Finaccurate and unfair."It is not
OL,16,Fpossible to say that, if the jury had
OL,17,Fbeen properly directed, they would
OL,18,Fhave been bound to return verdicts of
OL,19,Fguilty.
